metadata.name: Inertia #1429
metadata.description:
This project will be reserved and free for 48 hours, for all the holders of any of my projects!

The amount of reserves for each user will be equal to the amount of all the token held at 13:00 CEST [UTC+2] (May 23)
(example: user holds 3 "Figment" and 2 "ACCUMULATOR", will be able to mint "Inertia" 5 times)

48h from now I will update the reserves list and burn the remaining tokens

WARINING: The reserves will expire 48h after the drop! And a price for the unlocked mintables will be set (unreserved mints will not be free).

---

"Inertia is a property of matter by which it continues in its existing state of rest or uniform motion in a straight line, unless that state is changed by an external force."

Particles are blasted from 2 to 4 sides of the canvas, each particle has its own mass and it has to traverse a friction-field, once it loses its momentum completely it stops and leaves a trace, adding or subtracting light from the canvas.

The friction-field has 18 possible mutation kinds.
Mutations are high-friction zones of various shapes.

Made just with JS on a canvas
right-click to save

metadata.description:
Compositions of shapes and noise, order and chaos. Where does order end and chaos begin?

- Press [ space ] or click to toggle animation
- Press [ r ] to reset
- Press [ s ] to save the current frame as a 3000x4000 PNG

Requires WebGL2

metadata.name: BERNARD #10
metadata.description:
Bernard is a generative character I created.

He loves math/graphing/painting and music.

He draws visuals and music in his own thoughts.

With up to 14 fingers of chord playing, Bernard will solo along with the chords under moderate to slow tempo.

Bernard has 96 editions, aside from the mix-colored version, there are 8 rare Positive and 8 rare Negative.

Be patient with Bernard and enjoy his music and painting.

100% generative audio & visual.

Best experience with Full-screen & Headphones.

Click/Tap as you like if you want to participate in the canvas.

<S> to save image at any moment you like

10% donation > P5JS

objkt.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I. #103

metadata.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I. #103
metadata.description:
Experimental generative collection that merges analog photography, AI, generative text, and algorithmic coding, by digging down into the essence and building blocks of the different artistic communication channels. 

This work engages with all aforementioned mediums in a joint manner, guided by a random process. It starts with a collection of analog photographs, shot on film and scanned that were later used as a training dataset in Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) training. This way, A.I. learns the main characteristics of film photography. In particular, it mimics its recognizable grain. Another type of pixel grain is added with the use of code and pixel shifting as well as digital manipulation. Finally, the last type of “grain” appears with the use of generative text where a different kind of A.I. was given a short description of the project and instructed to imagine the rest of the story. The fragmented and void of meaning parts of generative text are added to the images as one of the possible traits.

issuer.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I.
